Authors: Yasar Karatas, Sahika Liva Cengiz, Hasan Esen, Aysun Toker, Cigdem Savas
Title: Effect of Carvedilol on Secondary Damage in Experimental Spinal Cord Injury in Rats
Abstract: AIM: Previous studies have shown that carvedilol has a neuroprotective effect in animal models of brain ischemia and brain oxidative damage in vitro. This study was perfomed to investigate the effect of carvedilol on the secondary damage in experimental spinal cord injury (SCI).
